    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Malverne was originally settled by the Rockaway Indians, with Ocean Avenue tracing an ancient Indian path.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malverne%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village’s name evolved from Norwood to Malverne, a change prompted by a need to avoid duplication with another Norwood in upstate New York.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malverne%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1895 the New York Bay Extension Railroad began a line through Malverne, later joining other lines to become part of the Long Island Railroad.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
